value.0: CRAZY BITS
O My Lords and Ladies... you need our help. Go and see Brother Therdan down the corridor, he'll clear your brain. Well, he'll try to... I'm sure.
Welcome, <brother/sister>. What can I do for you?
Make sure you hunt when it hunts itself: at night. It seems to prefer the deeper forest and is almost never seen at the coast.
You are truly blessed! Here, take this as a gift.

The Lord of Blackmoor liked to hunt. He had a large pack of particularily vicious Luskan hunting dogs that he raised on the flesh of his many victims. So accustomed to human flesh they became that they refuse to eat anything else. I just heard rumours that one is haunting the forest right now. Hunt it down and bring me its head.

Lord Blackmoor was a demon worshipping psychopath who terrorised his subjects into obedience. May the Gods curse his soul for eternity. Unfortunately, the memory of his foul deeds lingers on, poisoning the forest and giving rise to all kinds of unholy creatures.

This is a haven for the unfortunates driven to madness by the horrors that haunt these forests. There are things out there that would drive the best of men utterly insane. We try to treat the victims as well as we can...
You have been lucky indeed, my friend!
Welcome, <brother/sister>. What can I do for you?

This is a haven for the unfortunates driven to madness by the horrors that haunt these forests. There are things out there that would drive the best of men utterly insane. We try to treat the victims as well as we can...

You have been very lucky indeed, my friend.

I do have a request for you. Interested?

Castle Blackmoor, you mean. Yes, it has to do with that. Its Lord was a demon worshipping psychopath who terrorised his subjects into obedience. May the Gods curse his soul for eternity. Unfortunately, the memory of his foul deeds lingers on, poisoning the forest and giving rise to all kinds of unholy creatures.
You must not go to the castle then! There are artifacts there with immeasurable power that would make you ... very powerful!

Well, better a sane coward than a brave lunatic, I guess.

I do have a request for you, though. Interested?

That is very brave of you, my friend. Don't worry, we have a special room for frustrated crusaders... just in case you don't succeed like the ones before you. Take my advise: stay away from the castle.

I do have a request for you, though. Interested?
True, I have some inmates that have taken a few steps too many. Fare thee well, Crusader.

The Lord of Blackmoor liked to hunt. He had a large pack of particularily vicious Luskan hunting dogs that he raised on the flesh of his many victims. So accustomed to human flesh they became that they refuse to eat anything else. I just heard rumours that one is haunting the forest right now. Hunt it down and bring me its head.
*Dribble and/or make strange noises. Lord Nasher immitations are also proper way to make clear your as mad as a pig's arse.*
Pweep!
Ummm... goodbye!
I haven't found that damned dog yet... it's elusive!
Thanks, that'll help.
I returned with the Blackmoor Hound's head!
Thank you!
What was the story about those dogs again?
What can you tell me about Lord Blackmoor?
What is this place?
Thank you for the information!
Interesting... can I ask another question?
Horrors? Insane? I have walked these forests and nothing happened to me!
Guess so, yes.
What is this place?
Horrors? Insane? I have walked these forests and nothing happened to me!
This is about the gloomy castle in the South-West, right? Castle Blackhorse, or what's the name again.
Interesting... but I must leave!
Unfortunately I am planning to add to the atmosphere! Muhahaha!
... really?
That sounds horrible.. and dangerous. Incidentally, is the boat that I saw below the asylum sea-worthy?
Nahhh
This will not do! I will cleanse the area right here and right now! The Light will be victorious!
No, you do not take seriously my Path to Enlightement!
Of course!
Hmm.. big bad dog, human flesh, Lord Blackmoor... sounds like trouble. I'll pass this one!
That doesn't seem to be too hard a task. I will do it!
